JENKINS SETUP AND PIPELINE CREATION (STEP BY STEP)

1 Install Java and Jenkins on Ubuntu
  After installing, start Jenkins using terminal:
  sudo systemctl start jenkins
  sudo systemctl enable jenkins

2 Open Jenkins in Browser
  Go to: http://localhost:8080

3 Get Initial Admin Password
  In terminal type:
  sudo su -
  cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
  Copy the password and paste it into the browser.

4 Setup Jenkins
  Click on "Install Suggested Plugins"
  Wait for all plugins to install.

5 Create Admin User
  Enter details like:
  Username: admin
  Password: admin
  Email: admin@example.com

6 Install Required Plugins (if needed)
  Go to Manage Jenkins → Plugins
  Install:

7 Create a Pipeline Job
  Go to Dashboard
  Click "New Item"
  Enter a name (example: MyPipeline)
  Select "Pipeline"
  Click OK

8 Configure Pipeline
  Scroll down to Pipeline section

  Write pipeline script like this:

  pipeline {
  agent any
  stages {  
    stage('Clone Repo') {  
        steps {  
            git branch: 'main', url: 'https://github.com/your-repo.git'  
        }  
    }  

    stage('Build') {  
        steps {  
            echo "Building project..."  
        }  
    }  

    stage('Test') {  
        steps {  
            echo "Running tests..."  
        }  
    }  
}  

9 Using Pipeline Syntax Generator
  Inside Jenkins click "Pipeline Syntax"
  Select "git"
  Enter repository URL
  Enter branch name (same as GitHub)
  Click Generate
  Copy and paste into pipeline script

10 Save and Run
   Click Save
   Click "Build Now"
   Open build → Console Output
